@page "/privacy"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy — Nornis</PageTitle>

<article class="nornis-public-page">
    <div class="nornis-eyebrow">Privacy Policy</div>
    <h1>Your world is yours</h1>
    <p class="nornis-public-updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
        Nornis stores what you give it: world names, sources (session notes, journals,
        transcripts, links), and the artifacts, facts, and storylines derived from them. Your
        account carries only what sign-in requires — a username, an email address, and the
        identifier from our sign-in provider. We do not store passwords.
    </p>

    <h2>How AI processing works</h2>
    <p>
        When you submit a source for extraction or ask the Loremaster a question, the relevant
        world content is sent to our AI provider (Azure OpenAI) to generate the response. That
        content is not used to train AI models. We record token counts, costs, and timing for
        each AI operation — visible to you on your world's Costs page — but we do not log
        prompt content.
    </p>

    <h2>Visibility inside a world</h2>
    <p>
        World content is visible only to that world's members, according to the visibility
        each item carries: private items to their creator, GM-only items to GMs, party-visible
        items to everyone in the world. By default a world has no public or anonymous access —
        a GM can choose to open a read-only public view, described next.
    </p>

    <h2>Public sharing</h2>
    <p>
        Public sharing is off by default. A world's GM can turn on a read-only public link —
        nornis.app/w/… — and switch it off again at any time. While it's on, anyone with the
        link can read the world without signing in or creating an account, but only its
        party-visible material: a public visitor is treated as an anonymous Observer, so private
        and GM-only items never appear. What's shared is limited to the world's Overview, Codex,
        Timeline, and Sessions. Turning public access off closes the link again.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <p>
        We don't sell your data. We don't share world content with third parties beyond the
        infrastructure needed to run the service (hosting, database, and AI processing). We
        don't use your world content for advertising or model training.
    </p>

    <h2>Deletion</h2>
    <p>
        Deleting a source, artifact, or world removes it from the working record. If you want
        your account and all associated data removed, contact us and we'll do it.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy: reach the maintainer through the project's repository.</p>
</article>
